The day before, the Flipboard founders had shown me Flipboard and put it on my iPad, and I was real impressed. They told me at the meeting, "Do not show it to anybody else," and that the round was closed. 

During lunch with Ashton, I pulled it out. I said, "I've got to show this to you." He instantly said, "I have to invest in this. Get them on the phone right now." During that lunch, the round was reopened, and they weren't even mad at me for showing it to him.

